yes, I know that I won't shut up about how incredible this green bean salad is! but guys, it is SO SO SO good. the green beans are super crunchy, the flavor is to die for, it's so super easy. ate it for dinner again last night and I couldn't be more obsessed! 
SUMMER GREEN BEAN SALAD
1 pound fresh green beans
⅓ cup toasted walnuts, chopped
⅓ cup crumbled blue cheese
DIJON DRESSING
1/4 cup lemon juice
2 tablespoons dijon mustard
1/2 cup extra virgin olive oil
pinch of salt
freshly cracked black pepper
1 tablespoon fresh chopped herbs

find the full recipe here on the blog: https://www.howsweeteats.com/2019/07/green-bean-salad/

node.title: Summer Green Bean Salad - The Best Ever!

This summer chickpea salad is seriously the BEST chickpea salad ever. Tons of you have been making it for years and it's a major staple in my kitchen. Chickpeas, grilled corn, tomatoes, lime, garlic, herbs - so much good stuff!

You need:
2 (15-ounce) cans chickpeas, drained and rinsed
4 green onions, thinly sliced
2 ears grilled corn, cut from the cob
1 pint cherry tomatoes, quartered
3 tablespoons chopped fresh basil
2 tablespoons snipped fresh chives
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/4 teaspoon pepper
3 tablespoons olive oil
2 tablespoons red wine vinegar
1 1/2 tablespoons honey
3 garlic cloves, minced or pressed
1 lime, juiced and zest grated

Find the full recipe here: https://www.howsweeteats.com/2014/06/the-simple-chickpea-salad-im-losing-my-mind-over/

This is one of our favorite easy dishes to make in the summer! You can make it ahead of time too. It's SO GOOD. Full recipe below... 8 ounces pasta, boiled and cooled
1 pint grape tomatoes, halved
8 ounces fresh mozzarella balls, chopped
1 big handful fresh basil, chopped 
3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar 
1 garlic clove, minced 
1 tablespoon diced shallot
Pinch of dried basil and oregano 
Pinch of salt and freshly cracked pepper
1/3 to 1/2 c extra virgin olive oil 
In a large bowl stir together the pasta, tomatoes, mozzarella and fresh basil. 
Whisk together the vinegar, garlic, shallot, dried herbs, salt, pepper and olive oil.

Drizzle half of the dressing into the pasta. Toss well. Drizzle the rest right before serving. Garnish with extra fresh basil. Taste and season with salt and pepper if necessary! This stores great in the fridge.
